  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">There is currently global momentum for a tax on the financial sector. A substantial tax on the banks must be seen as a vital part of rebalancing the relationship between society and the financial sector and creating a fairer society  - we must continue to push home the link between taxing the banks and fighting poverty. It cannot be seen as enough to simply tax the banks, it must be recognised that the tax needs to raise hundreds of billions every year and be spent helping the poor at home and abroad.</narrative>
  </description>
